gas burner:<\/strong> turn the burner to high heat and hold a pepper with tongs over the flame turning occasionally until all sides are charred and the peppers are soft. <br><strong>Grilling in the oven:<\/strong> preheat the oven to 200°C  and grill peppers turning occasionally until all sides are charred and the flesh is soft. <br>Remove from the heat and transfer to a sealable heat resistant plastic bag, seal and leave to rest for <b>10 minutes<b> then peel off the skin and any charred edges.","If you prefer a smoother texture at the end of <b>step 3<b> blend <strong>20 sec\/speed 9<\/strong>.","This sauce can be served as a dip with pitta bread, spread on flatbreads, mixed into stews or served with pasta or potatoes, in which case you can omit the bread crumbs."],"basicInfo":["easy","5m","5m","1"]}